title: [altair-devnet-1] Validator proposed invalid signature block
body:
**Describe the bug**

Our validator missed proposing a block from the chain explorer: https://altair-devnet-1-explorer.ethdevops.io/block/49225

The log said
```
 Jul-22 08:05:00.805 [CHAIN]           ^[[31merror^[[39m: Block error slot=49225 code=BLOCK_ERROR_INVALID_SIGNAT        URE
2903514 Error: BLOCK_ERROR_INVALID_SIGNATURE
2903515     at processBlocksInEpoch (/usr/app/node_modules/@chainsafe/lodestar/src/chain/blocks/process.ts:137:15)
2903516     at processBlock (/usr/app/node_modules/@chainsafe/lodestar/src/chain/blocks/process.ts:42:3)
2903517     at processBlockJob (/usr/app/node_modules/@chainsafe/lodestar/src/chain/blocks/processor.ts:59:5)
2903518     at Object.job (/usr/app/node_modules/@chainsafe/lodestar/src/chain/blocks/processor.ts:38:42)
2903519     at Timeout._onTimeout (/usr/app/node_modules/@chainsafe/lodestar/src/util/queue/index.ts:106:22)
```

**Expected behavior**

Lodestar validator should propose valid block

there are a lot of blocks like that: 49284, 49292, 49341, 49347, 49350 ...
it could be the same issue to #2878

I was able to catch an invalid signature signed block proposed by us
[invalid_sig_signed_block_69778.zip](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/files/6875307/invalid_sig_signed_block_69778.zip)
[preState_slot_69778.zip](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/files/6875308/preState_slot_69778.zip)

if we use the above pre state to verify signatures for the above block, we'll see the invalid signature comes from the sync committee signature set, it's likely we have an issue when create `SyncAggregate`
